-- pd.package: FTD virgil-font package
name: fastn-community.github.io/virgil-font

This FTD font `virgil-font` package is for your ftd web projects. To Use this
virgil-font inside `FTD` project follow below instructions.

-- ds.h3: How to use virgil-font?

-- ds.code: Add this to your FASTN.ftd
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: fastn-community.github.io/virgil-font

-- ds.markdown: 

After adding virgil-font dependency inside your `FASTN.ftd` file, You need to
add virgil-font assets and import it inside your `.ftd` files where you are
using this font for your custom font types. 

To include virgil-font into your `ftd` file follow below instructions.

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- import: fastn-community.github.io/virgil-font/assets as virgil-font-assets


-- ds.h3: How to create a custom virgil-font type? 

-- ds.markdown: 

We don't recommend creating custom types. We recommend to use 
our [virgil-font-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/virgil-font-typography)

If you're using [virgil-font-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/virgil-font-typography) 
and still your designer has introduced new font size which are not included or 
part of our [virgil-font-typography](https://fastn-community.github.io/virgil-font-typography) 
then only define custom types. 

We hope you shouldn't need to define a custom type.

Below is an example of creating a custom `ftd.type` using virgil-font.

-- ds.rendered:

-- ds.rendered.input:

\-- ftd.type virgil-font-size-12-desktop:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $virgil-font-assets.fonts.virgil


\-- ftd.type virgil-font-size-12-mobile:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $virgil-font-assets.fonts.virgil

\-- ftd.responsive-type virgil-font-size-12-400:
desktop: $virgil-font-size-12-desktop
mobile: $virgil-font-size-12-mobile

\-- ftd.text: 
role: $virgil-font-size-12-400
color: $inherited.colors.text-strong

`font-size: 12px, font-weight: 400` 

üëâ The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog 

-- ds.rendered.output:

